-- Lesson: Where Do You Live Right Now? (6 blocks, 1 min)
UPDATE lessons
SET content_json = '{"estimated_minutes":1,"blocks":[{"type":"heading","content":"Where Do You Live Right Now?"},{"type":"text","content":"*A self-assessment from the Zones of Resilience*"},{"type":"text","content":"Most people think of emotional regulation as a trait — something you either have or you do not. It is not. It is a *zone* you move through over the course of a week, a day, a conversation. This assessment tells you which zone you are living in most often right now."},{"type":"text","content":"It is not a test. There are no wrong answers. Your zone is *temporarily accurate*, not who you are. Tomorrow, it might be different."},{"assessment_id":"zones-resilience","title":"The Zones of Resilience Self-Assessment","intro":"For each of the ten statements below, mark the option that is most true for you over the last seven days. Be honest with yourself — your partner will not see this unless you show them. Then answer the directional question at the bottom, and we will tell you which zone you are living in right now.\n","questions":[{"id":"q1","text":"I can feel my body calming down within ten minutes of a hard conversation.","type":"likert-4","options":["Rarely","Sometimes","Often","Almost Always"]},{"id":"q2","text":"When my partner says something that stings, I can pause before I respond.","type":"likert-4","options":["Rarely","Sometimes","Often","Almost Always"]},{"id":"q3","text":"I can hear my partner''s point of view even when I disagree with it.","type":"likert-4","options":["Rarely","Sometimes","Often","Almost Always"]},{"id":"q4","text":"I notice what my body is doing before my words come out.","type":"likert-4","options":["Rarely","Sometimes","Often","Almost Always"]},{"id":"q5","text":"When a fight is over, I can come back to my partner within an hour.","type":"likert-4","options":["Rarely","Sometimes","Often","Almost Always"]},{"id":"q6","text":"I can tell the difference between being activated and being mean.","type":"likert-4","options":["Rarely","Sometimes","Often","Almost Always"]},{"id":"q7","text":"I can ask for what I need without making my partner wrong first.","type":"likert-4","options":["Rarely","Sometimes","Often","Almost Always"]},{"id":"q8","text":"I can name what I am feeling in the moment I am feeling it.","type":"likert-4","options":["Rarely","Sometimes","Often","Almost Always"]},{"id":"q9","text":"I can apologize without a \"but\" attached.","type":"likert-4","options":["Rarely","Sometimes","Often","Almost Always"]},{"id":"q10","text":"I feel like myself during most conversations with my partner.","type":"likert-4","options":["Rarely","Sometimes","Often","Almost Always"]}],"directional_question":{"id":"direction","text":"Over the last seven days, when you have felt ''off,'' which direction does your body tend to go?","options":[{"id":"hyper","label":"Hotter, faster, louder, more reactive. When stress hits, my system presses the gas pedal."},{"id":"hypo","label":"Slower, heavier, quieter, more withdrawn. When stress hits, my system presses the brake pedal."},{"id":"both","label":"Both, depending on the day."}]},"scoring":{"method":"sum_likert_4_plus_direction","bands":[{"min":10,"max":16,"direction":"hyper","zone":"red"},{"min":10,"max":16,"direction":"hypo","zone":"blue"},{"min":10,"max":16,"direction":"both","zone":"mixed_low"},{"min":17,"max":24,"direction":"hyper","zone":"yellow_hyper"},{"min":17,"max":24,"direction":"hypo","zone":"yellow_hypo"},{"min":17,"max":24,"direction":"both","zone":"mixed_mid"},{"min":25,"max":40,"direction":"hyper","zone":"green"},{"min":25,"max":40,"direction":"hypo","zone":"green"},{"min":25,"max":40,"direction":"both","zone":"green"}]},"results":{"red":{"title":"Red Zone — Full Activation","body":"Your body is hitting the gas to survive. Adrenaline is flooding your system. Heart racing, chest tight, thoughts narrowed. Your Critter Brain has the wheel, and your CEO Brain is offline because logic and love do not matter when your body thinks it is in danger. You are not choosing to lose control. You are just trying to stay alive. The Red Zone is your nervous system doing its job — protecting you from what it has decided is a threat.\n","next_step":"Go to The 30-Second Reset now. Cold water on your wrists also helps. Do not try to repair the conversation from the Red Zone — you do not have access to the part of your brain that can.\n"},"yellow_hyper":{"title":"Yellow Hyper Zone — Early Activation","body":"You can feel your system revving up. Something small suddenly starts to feel big. Your jaw is tight, your foot is tapping, your chest is warm. You are not in full fight-or-flight yet — but the Critter Brain has perked up and the CEO Brain just dimmed the lights. This is an early warning signal. Your body is telling you \"System warming up — please intervene.\" If you catch it here, regulation is much easier than after full Red Zone activation.\n","next_step":"Unclench your jaw. Drop your shoulders. Take one long exhale, twice as long as your inhale. Whisper to yourself, \"This is energy. I''m okay.\"\n"},"green":{"title":"Green Zone — Home Base","body":"Your body is steady and grounded; your mind is clear; your heart is open. You are calm yet alert, peaceful yet engaged. Your CEO Brain is back at the wheel, calm and in control. This is your optimal state — the space where safety, clarity, and connection live. When both partners are in Green, connection feels natural and repair happens faster.\n","next_step":"Notice it. Anchor it. What does your Green Zone feel like in your body? Where do you feel warmth or ease? Remembering what Green feels like is how you find your way back the next time you leave it.\n"},"yellow_hypo":{"title":"Yellow Hypo Zone — Early Shutdown","body":"A deep fatigue is setting in. You are still functioning, but everything feels heavier — like you are moving through molasses. You are zoning out mid-conversation, scrolling your phone instead of replying, saying \"I''m fine\" when you are clearly not. You crave quiet but do not know how to ask for it. You are not lazy. You are depleted. Your system is pressing the brakes before it fully powers down. This is your body asking for refueling, not more effort.\n","next_step":"Step outside for a few breaths of sunlight. Take a sip of water. Play one song with emotion in it. Do one small thing that reminds your body, \"I''m still here.\"\n"},"blue":{"title":"Blue Zone — Full Shutdown","body":"Beyond exhausted. Beyond overwhelmed. Your system has said, \"I''m done.\" Not sadness exactly — the absence of feeling. Your body is heavy, your mind is foggy, your heart is far away. Your partner asks if you are okay and you can barely find words. This is biology, not failure. Your nervous system shut down to protect you from overwhelm. The way out is not by pushing harder — it is through warmth, safety, and tiny sparks of life gently returning.\n","next_step":"Start with warmth. A blanket, sunlight, a warm drink, or holding your own hand. Let someone sit beside you without fixing you. Whisper softly, \"I''m still here. I just need time to come back.\"\n"},"mixed_low":{"title":"Red and Blue — A Mixed Pattern","body":"Your body is moving between Full Activation and Full Shutdown depending on the day. This is common and it is not a failure. It usually means your system is depleted overall — some days it burns hot, some days it goes dark. Both are your Critter Brain trying to protect you with the only tools it has left.\n","next_step":"On Red days, use the Red Zone reset. On Blue days, use the Blue Zone reset. The pattern itself is information — it says your system needs gentleness and rest more than anything else right now.\n"},"mixed_mid":{"title":"Yellow — In Both Directions","body":"Your body is flickering between Yellow Hyper and Yellow Hypo. You are on the edge — not fully dysregulated in either direction, but not fully home either. This is a good place to be because it is easier to course-correct from Yellow than from Red or Blue.\n","next_step":"Notice which direction you are going when you feel \"off.\" Use the Yellow Hyper reset (unclench, long exhale, 5 senses) when you are revving up. Use the Yellow Hypo reset (sunlight, water, gentle movement) when you are slowing down."}},"type":"assessment"},{"type":"text","content":"*The full Zones of Resilience teaching — the story of how this map came to be, and what it means for your day-to-day life — is in Chapter 4 in Part II of this kit.*"}]}'::jsonb
WHERE module_id = (
  SELECT m.id FROM modules m
  JOIN courses c ON c.id = m.course_id
  WHERE c.slug = 'rescue-kit'
    AND m.sort_order = 1
