-- Lesson: The Conflict Recovery Plan (5 blocks, 1 min)
UPDATE lessons
SET content_json = '{"estimated_minutes":1,"blocks":[{"type":"heading","content":"The Conflict Recovery Plan"},{"type":"text","content":"Fill this out within twenty-four hours of a hard conversation — not during, not a week later. Your body needs to be back online, but your memory needs to be fresh."},{"type":"text","content":"The prompts below are yours. Nobody else will see them unless you choose to share. The worksheet is not the work — the *noticing* is the work. Your answers will be saved so you can come back to them later, and so you can fill this out again after the next hard conversation."},{"form_id":"conflict-recovery-plan","title":"The Conflict Recovery Plan","fields":[{"id":"what_happened","label":"What happened","type":"textarea","rows":4,"placeholder":""},{"id":"body_before_speaking","label":"What I felt in my body before I spoke","type":"textarea","rows":4,"placeholder":"Tight chest? Heat in the face? Racing heart? A sinking feeling in the stomach? Something else?"},{"id":"critter_brain_story","label":"What my Critter Brain told me","type":"textarea","rows":4,"placeholder":"The story underneath the words — ''he''s going to leave me'', ''she never listens'', ''I''m too much''."},{"id":"wish_instead","label":"What I wish I had done instead","type":"textarea","rows":4,"placeholder":""},{"id":"spark_step","label":"The one SPARK step I want to try next time","type":"radio","options":["See","Pause","Acknowledge","Reconnect","Kindle"]},{"id":"want_to_say","label":"What I want to say to my partner when we are both back in our Green Zone","type":"textarea","rows":6,"placeholder":"Try starting with ''I love you, and...'' The ''and'' is important."}],"instructions":"When to fill this out. Within twenty-four hours. Not in the middle of a fight — you will not have access to the part of your brain that can think clearly. Not a week later — the details will have softened into a story you are telling yourself. Somewhere between is where the real work happens.\n\nWhether to share it with your partner. Only if they are in their Green Zone and have asked to see it. Handing this worksheet to an activated partner is not a repair — it is a second fight. You are writing this for you, not for them. That is not selfish. That is where the work begins.\n\nWhat to do with it after. Keep it. Re-read it before the next hard conversation. Notice when the patterns repeat. The worksheet is not the work — the noticing is the work.\n\nIf you are stuck on \"What my Critter Brain told me.\" Most people need two or three tries before they can hear what their Critter Brain is actually saying underneath. Try starting with: \"The story I was telling myself about my partner in that moment was…\" and let your answer finish the sentence.\n\nIf you fill this out and it feels like nothing changed. Fill it out again after the next hard conversation. And the one after. The pattern only shows up when you have three or four of these side by side. Come back to this page and fill it fresh each time — your answers will be saved.","type":"fillable_form"},{"type":"text","content":"*The Individual Reflection prompts in Chapter 5 (The SPARK Method) go deeper on what came up here. Come back to them when you are ready.*"}]}'::jsonb
